modules.description: Generates C stubs for OCaml foreign function interfaces based on provided configurations. It takes a list of configuration values specifying binding names, error handling policies, concurrency models, C headers, and binding modules. This module is used to automate the creation of low-level C bindings for OCaml libraries.

This module defines a function `rules` that generates build rules for Ctypes-based OCaml projects. It takes parameters such as installation directories, target OS, and library paths, and sets up the necessary compilation and linking steps. It is used to integrate Ctypes-generated bindings into a build system, ensuring correct handling of generated stubs and dependencies.
